<image width="33%" pi:generated="problems/images/mom-1057110-1.png"/><p>
Suppose a = 4 and b = 9. Calculate:</p>
<p>
c = <input type="text" style="width:25ch" name="qn1000" id="qn1000" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 1 of 3" class="text"/></p>
<p>
A = <input type="text" style="width:25ch" name="qn1001" id="qn1001" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 2 of 3" class="text"/> degrees</p>
<p>
B = <input type="text" style="width:25ch" name="qn1002" id="qn1002" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 3 of 3" class="text"/> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place. Give angles in <em>degrees</em>.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>9.8</li><li>24.0</li><li>66.0</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={4}^{{2}}+{9}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={16}+{81}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={97}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{97}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{9.8488578017961}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{9.8}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle A</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arctan{{\left(\frac{{4}}{{9}}\right)}}}\approx{23.962488974578}\approx{24}</m></p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{23.962488974578}^{\circ}\approx{66.037511025422}\approx{66}</m>.</p>

</solution>
